This year was a lot of things… I had a lot of surgeries, even more complications from said surgeries, I distracted myself by watching my child grow & thrive, spending quality time with my family, playing more live shows, and we traveled quite a bit!! Hoping to be a healthier, happier woman in ‘23!!
.
Cheers to all you guys out there struggling, but doing it anyways! I see you, and you’re doing great. Keep going 💜

0/10 for the norovirus diet. It works, I’m skinny af, but it’s zero fun. Will not be trying again.

I’m thrilled to share the news - I have an album coming out next month!! This is a collection of songs that I feel represents the woman I am today, the good, the complicated, and the fugly 😂 my partner on this is the one & only @derekgarten who really saw the vision I had & delivered 100%. 
.
Come celebrate with me on Sunday, September 24th at @tabardtheatre in downtown San Jose! Show starts at 4pm for you early birds, you’re welcome!! 
.
Pre-order will be available in 2 weeks.

Sometimes I think better on the floor. #songwriter

It’s here! I write a lot of songs, but sometimes I write one that feels so personal, or so special to me that I have to put my own name on it. This EP is a handful of songs so near and dear to me, I hope you enjoy listening to them as much as I enjoyed writing them!! 
.
Huge love & thank you’s to @derekgarten @primerecording and @nashvillemastering for breathing life into this project. Cheers to many more together!!

Album Release Show!! 
.
What a wonderful evening, you guys are the actual best. Actual friendship bracelets, and a 4pm start so we all made it home in time to tuck in our kids 😂 it was a day I’ll cherish forever. 
.
Thank you all for coming, for celebrating this project with me, and for always cheering me on!! Until next time….
In the blink of an eye 😍
36 (Mira’s Version)
Calling me wifey already? Seems fast, but ok.

ITS HERE! 
.
Sometimes, when I write songs, I can see the entire scene play out with every line we write. 
.
When @derekgarten and I wrote this, it sort of grew legs and started to walk on its own. There was something magical about how it all came together; the video felt that way too. 
.
Our director @devabfilms asked me about the song, we talked about it briefly & she came up with this entire vision and her & the entire team at @impactcreative absolutely knocked it out of the park. 
.
Please enjoy the video for “Enough to Try” out now. Swipe for BTS 😉 huge incredible thanks to all the moving parts that came together to bring this one to life!! 
.
Moving parts: @derekgarten @primerecording @devabfilms @philiplima @impactcreative @kalaketchum
